medical_history.chief_complaint: Acute exacerbation of post-operative abdominal pain
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: Symptoms began 8 hours prior to presentation; the patient is four days post-thrombectomy, arterioplasty and stenting of her left axillary-to-bifemoral jump graft. Symptoms have progressed to acute abdominal pain.
medical_history.past_medical_history: Atrial fibrillation, rheumatoid arthritis, coronary artery disease with history of myocardial infarction, osteoarthritis, history of lung cancer with chemotherapy and radiation therapy, gastroesophageal reflux disease, hypertension.
